b'I wish I had a river that I could skate away on."\n-Jeff Ament'

b"In the summer of 1993, we took the same plane between two Canadian cities and she sat across the aisle from me.  I reached into my backpack and put in a copy of Blue into my Walkman and couldn't believe the angel from these songs was a real human sitting across from me."

b"But, the record we listened to most was Joni Mitchell's Blue.  I know, for me, it made me feel less homesick.\nJoni was born and raised just over the border in Alberta and Saskatchewan from my north central Montana home, and everything she sang about I could visualize and feel."

b'Joni Mitchell BLUE is 50\n\n"In the early roommate days of PJ, Ed and I listened to a few tapes over and over, Rickie Lee Jones/Pirates, Fugazi/Steady Diet, Waterboys/This Is The Sea, Last Temptation of Christ, Eno/Discreet Music and a few others. https://t.co/H0Nn3cqEbG'

b'#RiverCross\n\n"This is another example of great songwriting, incredible singing and incredible lyrics. It\'s fun to do different styles of songs... At this stage of our career I think we\'ll be able to branch out even more than where we are now with this album." - Matt Cameron'

b'#RiverCross

"...I think the imagery he uses and stories he's telling there are universal... the simplicity of the harmony and the primalness of the melody just makes it an instant classic." - @SGossard

Watch the official visualizer for "River Cross": https://t.co/aZBV0aUwSV'

b'#Retrograde\n\n"We wanted to make it soar, so you hear big guitars, delayed keyboards... When Ed gets into it, it almost feels like him flying off a cliff, and the world falls out underneath him." - Josh Evans'

b'#Retrograde

"That song has a real cinematic vibe, and it's sort of an extension of what Mike can do when he just goes deep with the music that he's writing." - Jeff Ament

Watch the official music video for "Retrograde": https://t.co/56YppKyOv3'

b'#ComesThenGoes

"There was an electric guitar that got added from Ed at the last minute... just a little bit of power in a few spots and make sure the bridge chords are strong coming in." - @SGossard

"Sonically, it\xe2\x80\x99s simple, but emotionally, it is very complex." - Josh Evans'

b'#ComesThenGoes

"We listened to a version Eddie recorded, we were so moved by the lyrics. It was a moment for me in this whole recording process when he first shared that song with us." - Matt Cameron

Watch the official visualizer for "Comes Then Goes": https://t.co/LdWoPNEf0S'

b'#BuckleUp

"I guess that's what I was aiming for, juxtaposing something pretty with a somber lyric. I think it's pretty good... [Ed] just sang it really in the spirit of how I had it in the demo" - @SGossard

Watch the official visualizer for "Buckle Up": https://t.co/BNQ5TrIfX3'

b'#BuckleUp\n\n"What ended up on the record was pretty improvisational, it was counter melodies I was hearing. Stone & I have always worked well together in that way, complimenting each other\'s riffs & leaving space for one another and that was a really fun track..." \xe2\x80\x8b- Jeff Ament'

b'#TakeTheLongWay\n\n"Matt plays some guitar on the chorus but it ended up being mostly Mike playing the rhythm parts \xe2\x80\x94 those are his metal roots coming out. Stone plays that Mudhoney, fuzzed-out guitar stuff." - Josh Evans'

b'#TakeTheLongWay

"It was a big step for me to write a song, write the lyrics, come up with the melody, etc. I had this rhythm track kickin' around since 2016 or 2015." - Matt Cameron

Watch the official visualizer for "Take the Long Way": https://t.co/Ns0IGr2Hm6'

b'#NeverDestination

"I always think of that song as a surf rock song. Ed\xe2\x80\x99s vocals, lyrics & aggression were the north star for the song, so we built everything around that to keep it exciting." - Josh Evans

"I think the energy comes from the same place of Corduroy..." - @SGossard'

b'#NeverDestination

"Eddie recorded a demo, we tried to create some of those elements in the band version. It's a really great straight up rocker that fits really nice into the album." - Matt Cameron 

Watch the official visualizer for "Never Destination": https://t.co/N6ynpxBc70'

b'#SevenOClock\n\n"The performance you hear is pretty much a live take of the band playing together, certainly for the verses. The initial inspiration came on literally the first day we started recording this record." - Josh Evans'

b'#SevenOClock

"This song was almost kind of three different songs, I didn't have any expectations for it ... In the end it was Ed\xe2\x80\x99s perseverance with this track that got it to happen." - @SGossard 

Watch the official visualizer for "Seven O'Clock": https://t.co/JbdN0LkPgC'

b'#Alright\n\n"Lyrically what sort of came out was, to at all costs be selfish, even if it hurts the people that you love because your own life is the most important thing, it\'s the only way you can support the people you love." - Jeff Ament'

b'#Alright

"[Jeff's] demo, which he started at home in Montana, had that Kalimba loop that goes throughout the song, plus some of the piano chords and acoustic guitars." - Josh Evans

Watch the official visualizer for "Alright": https://t.co/xz96pkBsX0'

b'#QuickEscape\n\n"I remember hearing Jeff\'s demo and using the drum patterns that he and Josh came up with, and using that as a reference point and replacing the drum loop with acoustic drums." - Matt Cameron'

b'#QuickEscape

"The lyrics are so great... you immediately visualize the whole song because it's a great story... I can't wait to play that song live." - Jeff Ament   

Watch the official music video for "Quick Escape": https://t.co/lYo1keFj8H'

b'#DanceOfTheClairvoyants

"It felt like we cracked the code after this song... It makes such a statement." - Josh Evans

"One of the tracks I'm most proud of on this record because it was really collaborative in the weirdest way." - Jeff Ament'

b'#DanceOfTheClairvoyants

"It's fascinating to me at this point how music is a mood elevator, it's a quasi, spiritual moment... and there's a world to be explored." - @SGossard 

Watch the Mach III music video for "Dance of the Clairvoyants": https://t.co/Hg4t8p35Pv'

b'#SuperbloodWolfmoon

"This was another good example of Eddie's really awesome, king of Northwest garage style of songwriting." - Matt Cameron

"The subtlety of how those chords are played, and the energy that he [Ed] puts into that is really special." - @SGossard'

b'#SuperbloodWolfmoon

"...the experimental nature here is in the songwriting and the structure... what I was calling 'chorus,' Ed was calling 'verse.'... we realized it didn\xe2\x80\x99t matter." - Josh Evans

Watch the official music video for "Superblood Wolfmoon": https://t.co/1eEsBemrzD'

b'#WhoEverSaid\n\n"I think it was one of those songs that came together in the studio for us, we had a pretty rough outline of what the structure was and what Ed was looking for. It was a fun time recording this song because we were all in the studio together." - Matt Cameron'

b'#WhoEverSaid

"It\xe2\x80\x99s a great opening track for a record, cool arrangement, it's going to be a lot of fun to play." - @SGossard

Watch the official visualizer for "Who Ever Said": https://t.co/2lCIDCjSij'

b'Ticketing\n\nWe understand it is important to know how ticketing will work. Ticketmaster will be in touch shortly, but current tickets will be honored for the new dates.'

b'(10/10) Just as we look forward to our next concerts and the ability to gather together and play loud songs as energized as ever.

We are so sorry\xe2\x80\xa6
And deeply upset..

If anyone out there feels the same based on this news, we share that emotion with you.

- Ed & Pearl Jam'

b'(9/10) Again, here in Seattle what we are witnessing we would not wish for anyone. What we do wish for the rest of the country is that they can avoid the harsh negative effects of this and retain their sense of community and take care of one another.'
b'(8/10) Having no examples of our national health department\xe2\x80\x99s ability to get ahead of this, we have no reason to believe that it will be under control in the coming weeks ahead.'
b'(7/10) It certainly hasn\xe2\x80\x99t helped that there\xe2\x80\x99s been no clear messages from our government regarding people\xe2\x80\x99s safety and our ability to go to work.'

b'(6/10) Add to that we also have a unique group of passionate fans who travel far and wide. We\xe2\x80\x99ve always been humbled by this and respect their energies and devotion. However in this case, travel is something to avoid.'

b'(5/10) We\xe2\x80\x99ve worked hard with all our management and business associates to find other solutions or options but the levels of risk to our audience and their communities is simply too high for our comfort level.'

b'(4/10) So it is with deep frustration and regret that we are forced to make this most unfortunate of announcements...\n\nThis scheduled first leg of our PJ/Gigaton tour will need to be postponed and shows rescheduled for a later date.'

b'(3/10) Unfortunately, communing in large groups is a huge part of what we do as a band and the tour we\xe2\x80\x99ve been busy planning for months is now in jeopardy...\n\nWe have and will always keep the safety and well-being of our supporters as top priority.'

b'(2/10) It\xe2\x80\x99s been brutal and it\xe2\x80\x99s gonna get worse before it gets better. \n\nSo we are being told that being part of large gatherings is high on the list of things to avoid as this global health crisis is now beginning to affect all of our lives.'

b'(1/10) As residents of the city of Seattle, we\xe2\x80\x99ve been hit hard and have witnessed firsthand how quickly these disastrous situations can escalate. Our kids\xe2\x80\x99 schools have closed along with universities and businesses. https://t.co/SRcZasIVsk'
